All or Nothing;;2002;;R;;Drama;;7.5;;Mike Leigh;;Timothy Spall,Lesley Manville,Ruth Sheen,Alison Garland,Jean Ainslie,Badi Uzzaman,Parvez Qadir,Russell Mabey,Thomas Brown-Lowe,Oliver Golding,Henri McCarthy,Ben Wattley,Paul Jesson,Gary McDonald,Diveen Henry,Leo Bill,Peter Stockbridge,Brian Bovell;;Penny's love for her partner, taxi driver Phil, has run dry. He is a gentle, philosophical guy, and she works on the checkout at a supermarket. Their daughter Rachel cleans in a home for elderly people, and their son Rory is unemployed and aggressive. The joy has gone out of Phil's and Penny's life, but when an unexpected tragedy occurs, they are brought together to rediscover their love. All or Nothing is set in a London working-class housing estate over a long weekend, and also tells the stories of a range of Phil and Penny's neighbors, some of whom become involved in the family's lives, and all of whom experience an emotional journey.;;https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0286261/